body:
I have this error only on server side and when client closes connection only but not per each rpc call.

@jboeuf I have configured environment to test this behavior so once your patch is ready I will test it.
Unfortunately I am not an expert in SSL/TLS so I can't say exactly that patch solves the issue in right way or not. But I am sure that if there are no any issues with normal connection closing - there definitely shouldn't be any errors.

@maxkondr I definitely agree with your statement that if there is no issue with connection closing, there should not be any errors. I'll have a patch out shortly.

@alexodus do you have some logs on the java client side that would indicate what is going on? I recently removed some cipher suites in the core C stack that were not HTTP2 compliant (blacklisted). It may be that your java client cannot handle the compliant ones. 
The PR is https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/10772 
Maybe you can try to set the cipher suites manually with the env var: `GRPC_SSL_CIPHER_SUITES`
to the old default ones (which contains the blacklisted ones): `ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256:ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA256:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384`. Note that I don't recommend using the blacklisted cipher suites in production...

@alexodus thanks.
@maxkondr can you try the new patch?
 https://github.com/jboeuf/grpc/commit/ab9bc721304a289632ac1d224724f9174a0f471b
